{
  "text": "Chaos synchronization is an important topic in nonlinear science due to its extensive applications in many fields such as secure communication [CITATION_1] , complex network [CITATION_2] and neural science [CITATION_3] . A wide variety of synchronization phenomena have been proposed, including complete synchronization, anti-synchronization, projective synchronization, generalized synchronization, generalized projective synchronization (GPS), phase synchronization, generalized compound synchronization, fractional order synchronization, etc.",
  "citation_candidates": [
